{"questionId":"31992071","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is shown.</p>\n<p>The graph passes through the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/542c729a4844bf2d34b3c955478d0ebe6434cb42.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Describe fully these transformations, including the order in which they occur.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>vertical stretch scale factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The vertical stretch can occur in any order.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong><br>translation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> followed by horizontal stretch scale factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong><br>horizontal stretch scale factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> followed by translation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em> in either approach, for correct transformations, but incorrect order.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"31992071","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.10a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Describe fully these transformations, including the order in which they occur.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
